    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine equipped with individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system. This example is mechanically robust, with the critical rear subframe reinforcement and VANOS bulletproofing already addressed. Power is delivered through a crisp 6-speed manual transmission to a variable M differential lock, ensuring exceptional longitudinal and lateral grip. The suspension geometry remains true, providing the communicative steering and balanced chassis dynamics synonymous with the M-division. While the finish shows minor road-going patina, the powertrain and drivetrain are in excellent operational order for the discerning driver.",
