    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a 2005 Porsche 911 Carrera (997.1) featuring the 3.6L horizontally opposed flat-six engine paired with a precise 6-speed manual transaxle. This driver-focused example benefits from the M96/05 power unit with VarioCam Plus, ensuring optimal valve timing and lift for a broad torque curve. The suspension geometry features the characteristic MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear setup, maintaining excellent kinematic integrity. Stopping power is provided by four-piston aluminum monoblock calipers clamping cross-drilled rotors. The vehicle exhibits honest patina consistent with its mileage, but the powertrain remains robust with no signs of bore scoring or intermediate shaft bearing issues. A mechanically sound platform ready for the canyon or the track.",
